dct_description_sm: Bar scale on map given in "A scale of miles;" bar scales on inset maps given in "A scale of pases."
Decorative border and cartouches, compass rose, coats of arms (labeled).
Latin in pictorial inset to right.
Inset maps (bird's eye views): Barwick; Newecastle / described by William Mathew [1611-1612].
From Speed's Theatre of the Empire of Great Britain, 1676.
